Workshop page : http : / / dimlab . usc . edu / widm 99 CIKM'99 2 nd Workshop on Web Information and Data Management ( WIDM'99 ) Kansas City , Missouri , USA November 5 - 6 , 1999 In conjunction with ACM CIKM'99 : Eight International Conference on Information and Knowledge Management Sponsored by ACM SIGIR and SIGMIS Objectives - - - - - - - - - - Providing effective and efficient access to the vast information available on the web has become a critical research area in recent years . Further , large amounts of data reside in non-database applications such as desktop applications ( spreadsheet , word processors , etc . . . ) , E- mail messages , bibliography files ( such as BibTex ) , and , more generally , semi-structured and unstructured repositories . This workshop is intended to bring together researchers in the database and information retrieval areas to assess current methodologies and explore new approaches to the problems of the management and retrieval of information on the web and non-database repositories ; and the interoperability of databases and non-database information sources . Topics of Interest - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - The following is a non-exclusive list of topics of interest : Modeling of web and non-database repositories . Query languages for the web . Web query processing and optimization . Indexing techniques for web and non-database repositories . Web caching and prefetching . Resource discovery . Discovering structure in web and non-database repositories . Web site design . Emerging standards ( XML , RDF , etc ) for web data management . Information integration . Web navigation tracking . Web mining . Intelligent agents on web . Submission - - - - - - - - - - Submissions should be approximately 10 pages ( double-spaced ) in length . Papers will be reviewed by the program committee for their technical merit , originality , significance , and relevance to the workshop . The title page must include the name and email address of the contact author . We would only accept PostScript or PDF formats . Submit your papers in either of the following forms : 1 . ftp your paper to dimlab 2 . usc . edu . You can login to the host as anonymous user and save your file in / widm 99 directory . In order to avoid any name conflicts with other papers , please assign <first word of the title>_<your last name>_<your first name> as your file 's name . 2 . Send 4 hard copies of your paper no later than July 1 , 1999 to the program committee chair . Authors will receive notification of acceptance / rejection by August 1 . Final versions of the papers to appear in the proceedings published by ACM Press and are due on August 20 , 1999 . The workshop will be held on November 5 - 6 , 1999 .
